    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown</strong> <strong>onion[s]</strong></p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Bash your <strong>lemongrass </strong>with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sliced onion</strong>,<strong> pepper strips </strong>and <strong>bashed lemongrass stalk[s]</strong> to a deep baking tray (or oven-proof dish) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 5-10 min or until the onion has started to soften</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your<strong> creamed coconut roughly </strong>(if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong>, <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>ground paprika</strong>, <strong>red Thai</strong> <strong>curry paste</strong>, and a pinch<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>sugar </strong>in 500ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[700ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[900ml]</span><strong> boiled water </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> Thai red curry stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the onion has started to soften, pour the<strong> Thai red curry stock </strong>over the vegetables and put the tray back in the oven for 10-15 min or until the sauce has started to thicken</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is thickening, add your <strong>basmati rice</strong> and <strong>cauliflower rice </strong>to a pot with a lid with 160ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [250ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[</span><span class=\"text-purple\">300ml]</span> <strong>cold water </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the sauce has started to thicken, add your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> to the sauce and cook for 12 min further or until the fish is cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Season to taste with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once done, remove the <strong>lemongrass stalk</strong> and discard \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut & lemongrass baked fish curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/fragrant-coconut-and-lemongrass-baked-basa-curry-with-cauliflower-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>coconut & lemongrass baked fish curry</strong> with the<strong> cauliflower rice</strong> to the side</p><p>Tip: For fancy presentation, press the rice into a small bowl and turn out</p><p>Sprinkle over your<strong> crispy onions</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
